Package remodel.io

Interface TokenCodes

All Known Implementing Classes:
AssignmentExpression, BinaryExpression, CheckTokens, ConceptCompiler, ExpressionCompiler, ExpressionReader, ExpressionWriter, LiteralExpression, MetamodelReader, MetamodelWriter, ModelReader, ModelScanner, OperatorExpression, SymbolCompiler, TransformCompiler, TransformReader, TransformWriter, UnaryExpression
public interface TokenCodes
TokenCodes defines a set of token codes for the scanner. The token codes start from INPUT_END = -1 (the end of input marker), INPUT_START = 0 (the null byte, before any read, therefore the start of input marker), and the series proceeds from 1..n giving symbolic names to different kinds of symbol or identifier, real or integer number, literal string and character values, arithmetic and relational operators, as well as for other kinds of syntax including brackets and separators.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Anthony J H Simons, Qianhong Zheng

  • Method Details

    • toString

      static java.lang.String toString​(int code)
      Converts a token code into the symbolic name of the token. Searches the static Fields of this interface for a Field whose value is the same as the token code. Returns the Field's name if a match is found; otherwise returns null. Search is O(n) in the number of Fields.
      Parameters:
      code - a token code.
      Returns:
      the corresponding symbolic name, or null.
